&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROYAL NATIONAL ORTHOPAEDIC HOSPITAL NHS TRUST &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trust Doctor in Urology &amp; Neuro-Urology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an enthusiastic and experienced Specialty Doctor in Neuro-Urology for fixed term of 6 or 12 months. The role will include standard clinical activities of 40 hours per week, which will involve both outpatient care, procedure lists (in outpatient and theatre settings), diagnostic procedures, and ward rounds. The timetable will include a protected admin session, which is included in the PA allocation. The applicant will join a team of two consultants, one other specialty doctor and a compliment of specialist nursing staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Department of Neuro-Urology provides a comprehensive care to patients with spinal cord injuries, and also provides in-house support to inpatients across the rest of the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mr. &lt;strong&gt;Simon Warren - &lt;/strong&gt;Clinical Director - &lt;strong&gt;simon.warren@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
